Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning free-kick in a 3-1 win over Finland.
Jack Grealish opened the scoring in the first-half with a low finish into the bottom corner after a flicked pass from Angel Gomes.
Fredrik Jensen missed a crucial chance to equalize for Finland early in the second half.
Declan Rice finished well as he burst into the six-yard box to get on the end of Ollie Watkins’ low ball into the middle.
Arttu Hoskonen scored a consolation goal for Finland with a header from a corner.
Post-Match Reflections: England bounced back from their shock defeat to Greece.
Lee Carsley made six changes after the Wembley defeat.
Concerns remain about England's defense despite the win.
